title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.2: CHILD PROTECTION SYSTEMS

description.narrative: Increased equitable access to and utilization of child protection systems that prevent and respond to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect in programme districts., which contributes to Access To Justice, Birth Registration, Child Protection And Emergencies, Child Protection Systems, Data And Child Protection, Justice For Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable prevention of and response to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect of children and participation of adolescents

description.narrative: In 2020, birth registration services were strengthened through community leaders and midwives trained on birth registration procedures, and the civil registration system was improved with a renewed central information management system. Also, capacity building of social welfare workforce was enhanced, and emergency responses on prevention support services was strengthened to respond to the COVID-19 pandemic. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2021
